            <!-- lifecycle -->
            <article class="explorer-pane" data-pane="lifecycle">
              <div class="pane-head">
                <span class="pane-layer">L8</span>
                <h3 class="pane-name">Lifecycle &amp; back-pressure</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="pane-desc">The engine moves through a typed lifecycle and reports a recovery-health status, so an open that recovered with possible data loss comes back marked degraded. Under heavy write load, flushing takes priority over compaction, and writers are slowed before memory is exhausted to keep the engine within its memory budget.</p>
