  <!-- §7 · VECTOR ARCHITECTURE — per-slab progressive index on the LSM -->
  <section id="vector" class="pitch-section" aria-label="Vector architecture">
    <div class="pitch-wrap">
      <header class="sec-header reveal">
        <span class="sec-id"><span class="sec-hash">§</span>&thinsp;07<span class="sec-name">Vector Architecture</span></span>
      </header>

      <div class="sec-body">
        <div class="arch-intro reveal">
          <h2 class="sec-title">Vector Architecture</h2>
          <p class="sec-lead">The vector index is a derived artifact on the LSM, one per slab, and its kind changes by level: brute-force at the memtable, flat at the fresh L0 slabs, per-slab HNSW once a slab settles. Exact full-precision search stays the ground truth — the index only proposes candidates, an exact rerank decides the result, and a missing or corrupt index costs a rebuild, not a wrong answer.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="varch-top reveal" style="transition-delay: 90ms">
          <div class="vstack">
            <p class="vstack-tag">vector index · per slab · escalates by level</p>
            <div class="vlevel">
              <span class="vlevel-k">memtable</span>
              <span class="vlevel-holds">newest writes</span>
              <span class="vlevel-idx">brute-force · <em>exact</em></span>
            </div>
            <p class="vflow">↓ flush · build the cheap index</p>
            <div class="vlevel">
              <span class="vlevel-k">L0</span>
              <span class="vlevel-holds">fresh slabs</span>
              <span class="vlevel-idx">flat</span>
            </div>
            <p class="vflow vflow-key">↓ compaction · rebuild over live vectors · clean graph</p>
            <div class="vlevel">
              <span class="vlevel-k">L1</span>
              <span class="vlevel-holds">settled</span>
              <span class="vlevel-idx">per-slab HNSW</span>
            </div>
            <div class="vlevel vlevel-base">
              <span class="vlevel-k">L2</span>
              <span class="vlevel-holds">bulk</span>
              <span class="vlevel-idx">per-slab HNSW</span>
            </div>
            <p class="vstack-note">under a few thousand live vectors, skip the graph and brute-force. recall climbs as slabs settle into larger graphs.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="vquery">
            <figure class="pane-svg">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 360 136" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <text x="6" y="12" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7.5px;fill:var(--color-ink-low)">fan out · overfetch · rerank exactly</text>
                <rect x="6" y="56" width="54" height="36" rx="3" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <text x="33" y="72" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:8px;fill:var(--color-ink-hi)">query</text>
                <text x="33" y="83" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:6.5px;fill:var(--color-ink-low)">q · k · filter</text>
                <line x1="60" y1="74" x2="88" y2="35" style="stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.1" />
                <path d="M83 33 L90 34 L85 39 Z" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <line x1="60" y1="74" x2="88" y2="73" style="stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.1" />
                <path d="M84 70 L90 73 L84 76 Z" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <line x1="60" y1="74" x2="88" y2="111" style="stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.1" />
                <path d="M83 107 L90 112 L85 113 Z" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <rect x="92" y="22" width="82" height="26" rx="3" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <text x="99" y="38" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7.5px;fill:var(--color-ink-mid)">memtable</text>
                <text x="167" y="38" text-anchor="end" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7px;fill:var(--ember)">exact</text>
                <rect x="92" y="60" width="82" height="26" rx="3" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <text x="99" y="76" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7.5px;fill:var(--color-ink-mid)">slab</text>
                <text x="167" y="76" text-anchor="end" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7px;fill:var(--color-ink-low)">flat</text>
                <rect x="92" y="98" width="82" height="26" rx="3" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <text x="99" y="114" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7.5px;fill:var(--color-ink-mid)">slab</text>
                <text x="167" y="114" text-anchor="end" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7px;fill:var(--color-ink-low)">HNSW</text>
                <line x1="174" y1="35" x2="198" y2="61" style="stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.1" />
                <path d="M193 58 L200 60 L194 63 Z" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <line x1="174" y1="73" x2="198" y2="73" style="stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.1" />
                <path d="M194 70 L200 73 L194 76 Z" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <line x1="174" y1="111" x2="198" y2="85" style="stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.1" />
                <path d="M193 83 L200 85 L194 88 Z" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <rect x="200" y="49" width="100" height="48" rx="3" style="fill:var(--ember-soft);stroke:var(--ember);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <text x="250" y="64" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:8px;fill:var(--color-terracotta-700)">merge + exact rerank</text>
                <text x="250" y="76" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:6.5px;fill:var(--color-terracotta-700)">visibility · branch cap</text>
                <text x="250" y="86" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:6.5px;fill:var(--color-terracotta-700)">dedupe · full precision</text>
                <line x1="300" y1="73" x2="318" y2="73" style="stroke:var(--color-ink-mid);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <path d="M314 70 L320 73 L314 76 Z" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <rect x="320" y="58" width="36" height="30" rx="3" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-ink-hi);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <text x="338" y="76" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7.5px;fill:var(--color-ink-hi)">top-k</text>
              </svg>
            </figure>
            <p class="vq-cap">MVCC visibility and the branch fork cap are enforced in the merge, so the index never returns a row the read shouldn't see.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="varch-cards reveal" style="transition-delay: 140ms">
          <article class="crate">
            <p class="vcard-tag">lsm × hnsw</p>
            <h3 class="vcard-name">Compaction keeps the graph clean</h3>
            <p class="crate-desc">HNSW degrades as deletes and updates pile up; normally you rebuild it on a schedule. The LSM already rebuilds slabs and drops tombstones on every compaction, so each pass hands back a clean graph over only the live vectors. The re-index cost that sinks a graph at billion scale is cheap here, and recall climbs as slabs settle into larger graphs.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="crate">
            <p class="vcard-tag">the boundary</p>
            <h3 class="vcard-name">storage = WHEN · engine = WHAT</h3>
            <p class="crate-desc">Storage owns the slab lifecycle and an opaque artifact slot; on compaction it emits a rebuild event and commits the engine's bytes atomically with the slab. The engine owns the vector logic and hands back opaque bytes. The index is derived state: a missing or corrupt artifact rebuilds from the slab, so it can cost a rebuild, never data.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="crate">
            <p class="vcard-tag">the scale call</p>
            <h3 class="vcard-name">HNSW now, IVF at the ceiling</h3>
            <p class="crate-desc">At embedded scale (thousands to tens of millions of vectors per collection) the data fits in RAM and per-slab graphs are cheap to build, so HNSW is the default for its recall and latency. A configurable centroid/IVF mode is the scale-out path, for the rare deployment where re-index cost would dominate.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- §8 · HOW WE TEST -->
  <section id="testing" class="pitch-section" aria-label="How we test">
    <div class="pitch-wrap">
      <header class="sec-header reveal">
        <span class="sec-id"><span class="sec-hash">§</span>&thinsp;08<span class="sec-name">Testing Methodology</span></span>      </header>

      <div class="sec-body">
        <h2 class="sec-title reveal">Testing Methodology</h2>
        <p class="sec-lead reveal" style="transition-delay: 60ms">
          SQLite is the gold standard for testing an embedded database, and this harness is modeled on it: one bug class at a time, each with the technique that exposes it, every test checked against one recovery oracle.
        </p>

        <div class="approaches reveal" style="transition-delay: 110ms">
          <article class="approach approach-spine">
            <div class="approach-spine-text">
              <p class="approach-class">Recovery correctness</p>
              <p class="approach-desc">After any crash, what the database recovers must be a prefix of what it acknowledged: it may lose the most recent commits, but it must never leave a gap earlier in the history. A shadow model records every acknowledged commit, and one oracle checks the recovered state against that prefix after every fault the classes below inject.</p>
              <p class="approach-tag"><span>the oracle</span> every test verifies through it</p>
            </div>
            <div class="approach-spine-fig">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 250 116" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <text x="6" y="26" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:7.5px;fill:var(--color-ink-low)">ack</text>
                <line x1="54" y1="22" x2="214" y2="22" style="stroke:var(--color-line-hover);stroke-width:1" />
                <circle cx="54" cy="22" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="94" cy="22" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="134" cy="22" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="174" cy="22" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="214" cy="22" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <text x="6" y="66" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:8px;fill:var(--color-ink-hi)">prefix</text>
                <text x="238" y="67" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;fill:var(--color-ink-mid)">✓</text>
                <line x1="54" y1="62" x2="134" y2="62" style="stroke:var(--color-line-hover);stroke-width:1" />
                <circle cx="54" cy="62" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="94" cy="62" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="134" cy="62" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="174" cy="62" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-line-hover);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <circle cx="214" cy="62" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-line-hover);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <text x="6" y="104" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:8px;fill:var(--ember)">gap</text>
                <text x="238" y="105" text-anchor="middle" style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;fill:var(--ember)">✗</text>
                <line x1="54" y1="100" x2="114" y2="100" style="stroke:var(--color-line-hover);stroke-width:1" />
                <line x1="154" y1="100" x2="174" y2="100" style="stroke:var(--color-line-hover);stroke-width:1" />
                <circle cx="54" cy="100" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="94" cy="100" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="134" cy="100" r="5" style="fill:none;stroke:var(--ember);stroke-width:1.25;stroke-dasharray:2.5 2" />
                <path d="M130 96 L138 104 M138 96 L130 104" style="stroke:var(--ember);stroke-width:1.25" />
                <circle cx="174" cy="100" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-ink-mid)" />
                <circle cx="214" cy="100" r="4" style="fill:var(--color-panel);stroke:var(--color-line-hover);stroke-width:1.25" />
              </svg>
            </div>
          </article>

          <div class="approach-grid">
            <article class="approach">
              <p class="approach-class">Error paths</p>
              <p class="approach-desc">Fail the Nth backend operation, check that the engine recovers, then increment N until a full pass injects no new failure. Covers every reachable I/O call, plus disk-full and memory exhaustion.</p>
              <p class="approach-tag">fail-once · fail-continuously</p>
            </article>
            <article class="approach">
              <p class="approach-class">Hostile disks</p>
              <p class="approach-desc">Run on a disk model that injects torn writes, reordered appends, non-atomic renames, and garbage in an unsynced tail, then verify recovery under each.</p>
              <p class="approach-tag">four filesystem models</p>
            </article>
            <article class="approach">
              <p class="approach-class">Rare interleavings</p>
              <p class="approach-desc">A seeded scheduler randomises task order, the clock, and fault timing over the real lifecycle. Any failure prints its seed and replays bit-for-bit.</p>
              <p class="approach-tag">deterministic simulation</p>
            </article>
            <article class="approach">
              <p class="approach-class">Compound failures</p>
              <p class="approach-desc">Inject a second fault while recovery, compaction, or a checkpoint is still running. The engine must reach a valid state or return a typed, resumable error.</p>
              <p class="approach-tag">fail · resume · succeed</p>
            </article>
            <article class="approach">
              <p class="approach-class">Config divergence</p>
              <p class="approach-desc">Run the same workload under every mode, schedule, and budget; the results must be identical, and progress must stay bounded.</p>
              <p class="approach-tag">model-parity oracle</p>
            </article>
            <article class="approach">
              <p class="approach-class">Process drift</p>
              <p class="approach-desc">Merge-blocking CI: Miri and sanitizers, coverage and mutation thresholds that only ratchet up, nightly fuzzing, and a guard that fails if the test map goes stale.</p>
              <p class="approach-tag">miri · mutants · charter guard</p>
            </article>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- §9 · BENCHMARKS -->
  <section id="benchmarks" class="pitch-section" aria-label="Benchmarks">
    <div class="pitch-wrap">
